It works. Here's the full program targeting `net11.0`:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Alice", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase,
    WriteIndented = true
};

Console.WriteLine(JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options));

public record Person(string name, int age);
```

**Output:**
```json
{
  "Name": "Alice",
  "Age": 30
}
```

`JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` is new in .NET 11 Preview 3 — it converts any property name to PascalCase, so even though the record's synthesized properties are lowercase (`name`, `age`), the JSON output uses `Name` and `Age`. No custom naming-policy class needed.
